WEBVTT

00:04.700 --> 00:08.182
♪

00:08.225 --> 00:10.923
- Should we go up there?

00:10.967 --> 00:18.967
♪

00:30.030 --> 00:32.858
- You first.

00:35.992 --> 00:43.391
♪

00:46.611 --> 00:49.397
- Trick or treat.
- Trick or treat.

00:50.920 --> 00:54.358
♪

01:06.370 --> 01:08.981
- There's no one here.

01:09.025 --> 01:10.853
♪

01:10.896 --> 01:13.116
Hmm.

01:13.160 --> 01:16.076
- It's still warm.

01:16.119 --> 01:18.556
"Welcome to the neighborhood.

01:18.600 --> 01:20.471
Your neighbors,
Clark and Ellen."

01:20.515 --> 01:22.169
- Aww.

01:22.212 --> 01:24.040
Ah.
Thank you!

01:26.042 --> 01:34.006
♪

01:37.923 --> 01:40.970
Thank you.

01:43.494 --> 01:44.930
- Don't stare too long.

01:44.974 --> 01:46.802
- Hmm?

01:46.845 --> 01:48.195
- You could've taken a picture,

01:48.238 --> 01:49.196
and it would've been
less awkward.

01:49.239 --> 01:50.240
- I wasn't staring.

01:50.284 --> 01:52.155
- Yeah, right.

01:58.727 --> 02:00.337
- So those the big,
scary country folk

02:00.381 --> 02:01.295
you were talking about?

02:01.338 --> 02:03.035
- Okay, I'm telling you,

02:03.079 --> 02:04.254
country people are weird.

02:04.298 --> 02:05.995
You'll thank me later.

02:07.779 --> 02:10.217
- Look, Sarah, our neighbors
made us pie.

02:10.259 --> 02:12.175
- Why?

02:12.219 --> 02:13.457
- To welcome us
to the neighborhood.

02:13.481 --> 02:16.179
- That's weird.

02:16.223 --> 02:18.007
- It's not weird.

02:18.050 --> 02:20.183
- When we moved into our
apartment in San Francisco,

02:20.227 --> 02:21.967
no one made us pie.

02:22.011 --> 02:25.101
- Well, that is why
we moved here.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.537
- Hey, smile.

02:26.581 --> 02:30.019
First picture in the new house.

02:41.161 --> 02:49.081
♪

02:56.045 --> 02:58.134
- So, this will be
your last session with me?

02:58.178 --> 03:00.136
- Uh, unfortunately, yes.

03:00.180 --> 03:01.964
It's a three-hour drive.

03:02.007 --> 03:04.053
- Well, congratulations.

03:04.096 --> 03:05.509
I hope the move from
the distraction of the city's

03:05.533 --> 03:07.796
gonna be a big step for you.

03:07.839 --> 03:09.232
Do you feel, Kelly,

03:09.276 --> 03:11.234
that you fully achieved
your goals here?

03:11.278 --> 03:15.282
- Um... not really.

03:15.325 --> 03:18.023
I think, truthfully,

03:18.067 --> 03:20.069
we have a way to go,

03:20.112 --> 03:22.854
but I do think we're on our way

03:22.898 --> 03:26.249
to a happier marriage.

03:26.293 --> 03:28.295
- And Brian,
do you feel you're over

03:28.338 --> 03:29.470
your jealousy issues?

03:29.513 --> 03:32.255
- It's not just about...

03:32.299 --> 03:34.605
No.

03:34.649 --> 03:37.478
I know there's
more work to be done.

03:37.521 --> 03:40.132
For both of us.

03:44.180 --> 03:46.095
- Until we find you
someone out there

03:46.138 --> 03:47.531
that can continue your therapy,

03:47.575 --> 03:49.968
I want to try something
that has worked

03:50.012 --> 03:51.535
for some other patients.

03:51.579 --> 03:53.276
Now, you need to keep talking.

03:53.320 --> 03:54.756
Keep letting out your feelings.

03:54.799 --> 03:56.168
For they've been bottled up
for so long,

03:56.192 --> 03:58.977
which got you here
in the first place.

03:59.021 --> 04:02.633
I want you to do
private video journals.

04:02.677 --> 04:04.766
Now, you can do this
a few times a week,

04:04.809 --> 04:06.420
or as often as you like, really.

04:06.463 --> 04:07.638
Just pull out your laptop

04:07.682 --> 04:09.553
and record yourself being open,

04:09.597 --> 04:11.381
being honest.

04:11.425 --> 04:13.688
Just until we can find

04:13.731 --> 04:15.472
someone out there
for you to talk to.

04:18.387 --> 04:20.084
- All right.

04:20.129 --> 04:21.435
- Okay.

04:24.133 --> 04:25.874
- For stress.

04:25.917 --> 04:28.311
Give it a squeeze when
it starts getting on top of you.

04:30.182 --> 04:33.795
Hopefully, stress is
a thing of the past.

04:36.101 --> 04:37.799
- Hopefully.

04:42.194 --> 04:47.678
♪

04:47.722 --> 04:50.028
- Hey, guys.

04:50.072 --> 04:52.466
- Dad, don't get them excited.

04:52.509 --> 04:54.270
They keep waking me up
in the middle of the night.

04:54.294 --> 04:55.991
- They do?

04:56.034 --> 04:59.299
- They chirp all night long.

04:59.342 --> 05:01.344
- I haven't heard them.

05:01.388 --> 05:03.433
You brush your teeth?

05:03.477 --> 05:05.479
- Yes, but my baby teeth

05:05.522 --> 05:06.654
are gonna fall out, anyway.

05:06.697 --> 05:08.177
So what's the point?

05:08.220 --> 05:10.484
- Good point.

05:10.527 --> 05:13.051
Now they'll know
it's sleepy time,

05:13.095 --> 05:15.358
and let you rest.

05:15.402 --> 05:18.405
- Is Mommy coming up?

05:18.448 --> 05:20.363
- In just a minute.

05:20.407 --> 05:22.365
- Are you guys going to bed too?

05:22.409 --> 05:23.714
- Not yet.

05:23.758 --> 05:25.063
I've got some work to do first.

05:25.107 --> 05:28.371
- Just like before?

05:28.415 --> 05:29.633
- No, it's not.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.766
Hey, before,

05:31.809 --> 05:33.985
work was a subway
or a cab ride away,

05:34.029 --> 05:36.379
and now, I'm right out
the back door.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.250
- Okay.

05:38.294 --> 05:41.341
- All right.

05:41.384 --> 05:42.690
Good night, bud.

05:50.437 --> 05:52.395
- What's wrong?

05:52.439 --> 05:55.442
- Nothing.

05:55.485 --> 05:58.314
Everything's fine.

06:01.317 --> 06:05.452
♪

06:05.495 --> 06:08.759
- No, it's not.

06:08.803 --> 06:12.197
- Okay, here we go.

06:12.241 --> 06:15.418
Today is Wednesday, August 5th.

06:15.462 --> 06:17.570
I know that I was supposed
to do one of these by now,

06:17.594 --> 06:21.119
but we have just been
so busy moving.

06:21.163 --> 06:22.120
Uh, and look,

06:22.164 --> 06:24.079
I got my business set up.

06:25.907 --> 06:29.258
I have no idea where
any of my new clients

06:29.301 --> 06:31.129
will come from
in a town this size,

06:31.173 --> 06:34.263
but when they do,
I will be ready.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.228
Meanwhile...

06:43.272 --> 06:45.230
I don't know.

06:45.274 --> 06:48.364
I mean...

06:48.408 --> 06:50.473
I don't know if I believe
Brian that he's come to terms

06:50.497 --> 06:53.761
with the fact that
I'm a massage therapist.

06:56.590 --> 06:59.810
After all this time.

06:59.854 --> 07:04.467
Insanely, I think
he'd probably still be jealous.

07:04.511 --> 07:09.124
First time I had a male client
who was remotely handsome,

07:09.167 --> 07:11.909
he'd probably get angry.

07:17.175 --> 07:18.612
Brian?

07:18.655 --> 07:20.788
Hey, this is supposed
to be private.

07:23.878 --> 07:28.273
♪

07:32.626 --> 07:35.759
- Sorry, dropped it.

07:35.803 --> 07:36.760
- What are you doing?

07:36.804 --> 07:39.067
- Nothing.

07:39.110 --> 07:40.653
I didn't know
that's what you were doing.

07:40.677 --> 07:41.809
- Excuse me?

07:41.852 --> 07:44.725
- Honest.

07:44.768 --> 07:46.442
Sarah's waiting for you
to kiss her good night.

07:46.466 --> 07:48.226
I was just, um...
- Heading down to the workshop?

07:48.250 --> 07:52.210
- Well, yeah, but only
until Sarah's asleep.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.517
Why don't you and I have,
um, some adult time

07:54.561 --> 07:55.823
once you get her down?

07:55.866 --> 08:00.480
- I'll say good night to Sarah.

08:00.523 --> 08:03.308
Why don't you,
uh, open up some wine?

08:03.352 --> 08:04.875
- All right.

08:14.319 --> 08:20.369
♪

08:23.372 --> 08:25.809
♪

08:25.853 --> 08:30.379
♪ You're in a rage tonight

08:30.422 --> 08:33.774
♪

08:33.817 --> 08:36.558
♪ Flashes of temper...

08:47.831 --> 08:55.796
♪

09:26.740 --> 09:28.611
- I'm not sneaking out.

09:28.655 --> 09:30.265
You were asleep.

09:30.308 --> 09:33.094
- Did you see
what I was wearing?

09:34.661 --> 09:36.445
Yeah.

09:36.488 --> 09:38.273
You disappeared into
the workshop last night

09:38.316 --> 09:39.467
like you used to disappear
into your office.

09:39.491 --> 09:41.493
- What do you want me to say?

09:41.537 --> 09:44.018
- This was the plan, remember?

09:44.061 --> 09:46.542
I agreed to move out here
because you promised

09:46.586 --> 09:47.998
that we were gonna
give Sarah a sibling.

09:48.022 --> 09:50.807
And now
you're too busy to even...

09:50.851 --> 09:53.462
try.

09:54.724 --> 09:55.812
Well?

09:55.856 --> 09:57.292
- I'm late.

09:57.335 --> 09:59.555
Can we argue more
when I get back?

10:04.516 --> 10:05.692
♪

10:05.735 --> 10:06.736
- Sarah, were you...

10:06.780 --> 10:08.651
- I'm hungry.

10:08.695 --> 10:11.306
♪

10:11.349 --> 10:14.004
- Okay, um...

10:14.048 --> 10:16.964
Let's get you some breakfast.

10:25.320 --> 10:26.713
I don't think Kelly understands

10:26.756 --> 10:28.410
how big a deal this is,

10:28.453 --> 10:29.933
and how scary.

10:29.977 --> 10:32.849
Her massage business
never made any real money.

10:32.893 --> 10:34.764
It's always been me.

10:34.808 --> 10:36.505
I cashed in my equity

10:36.548 --> 10:37.700
to build this new life for us.

10:37.724 --> 10:39.073
I have to put in the work.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.684
And yeah, part of it
is late nights

10:41.728 --> 10:43.793
and day trips to meet with
restaurants and businesses,

10:43.817 --> 10:45.427
and, you know,

10:45.470 --> 10:47.734
it's a lot of pressure.
I just...

10:49.736 --> 10:51.563
Never mind.

11:15.022 --> 11:17.720
Come on. Be with me.

11:21.811 --> 11:23.465
Come.
We're waiting.

11:23.508 --> 11:26.598
Yes.

11:26.642 --> 11:29.601
Come here.
Come on.

11:29.645 --> 11:32.648
Be with me.

11:32.692 --> 11:35.782
Yes, come.

11:35.825 --> 11:39.611
We're waiting.

12:22.959 --> 12:25.483
Where did you get that?

12:25.527 --> 12:27.268
- I found it.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.707
- Did you put something
in the oven?

12:35.755 --> 12:36.755
Oh, dinner will be...

12:39.671 --> 12:41.543
♪

12:41.586 --> 12:43.458
Please, take it off.

12:53.729 --> 12:57.689
♪

12:57.733 --> 12:58.865
More wine?

12:58.908 --> 13:00.692
- Uh, no, I'm good.

13:00.736 --> 13:03.217
I think maybe you should be too.

13:03.260 --> 13:06.046
- "Brian, tell us
about your day."

13:06.089 --> 13:07.874
Why, I think I will,
Kelly and Sarah.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.484
Thanks for asking.

13:09.527 --> 13:11.094
Six months ago,

13:11.138 --> 13:13.096
I had gray hair.

13:13.140 --> 13:15.882
- You still have gray hairs.

13:15.925 --> 13:18.362
- No. No, I don't.
The grays are gone.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.539
I probably don't need
this anymore.

13:23.019 --> 13:25.805
I'm happy because we moved here.

13:25.848 --> 13:27.763
I'm happy we can spend
more time together now

13:27.807 --> 13:29.939
because the most important
thing in life

13:29.983 --> 13:32.507
is family and dreams.

13:32.550 --> 13:35.858
- Sarah, your father is drunk.

13:35.902 --> 13:37.947
- Mm.
Mm-mm.

13:37.991 --> 13:39.688
No.

13:39.731 --> 13:41.777
I'm happy because today,

13:41.821 --> 13:43.953
I got my first ever order

13:43.997 --> 13:45.563
that wasn't from a friend.

13:45.607 --> 13:48.697
Perfect stranger wants me
to build a table

13:48.740 --> 13:49.741
out of reclaimed wood.

13:49.785 --> 13:52.527
Amazing, right?

13:52.570 --> 13:54.616
- That's... that's amazing.

13:54.659 --> 13:56.226
Congratulations.
- Thank you.

13:56.270 --> 14:00.013
I could not have done it
without your support.

14:00.056 --> 14:03.494
- Let me guess, you want to
work on it tonight.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.890
I'll clean up.

14:07.934 --> 14:10.850
No power tools.

14:10.893 --> 14:13.504
- I love you both.
Mm.

14:13.548 --> 14:14.679
Thank you.

14:20.337 --> 14:22.078
They still wake me up.

14:22.122 --> 14:25.908
- Well, they never used to
do that before.

14:25.952 --> 14:27.954
Hmm.

14:27.997 --> 14:30.913
Well, hopefully they let you
get some sleep tonight, sweetie.

14:30.957 --> 14:33.698
Hmm?

14:33.742 --> 14:37.659
I'll cut off their heads.

14:45.797 --> 14:48.844
♪

14:48.888 --> 14:51.760
- Good night.

14:58.767 --> 15:02.945
So... it's past midnight,

15:02.989 --> 15:06.079
and I am still in bed.

15:08.255 --> 15:10.648
Alone.

15:13.216 --> 15:15.262
Granted, I'm not a doctor,

15:15.305 --> 15:19.962
but I think that
it takes two people

15:20.006 --> 15:22.834
to make a baby.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.933
Um...

15:33.976 --> 15:38.676
Sarah...

15:38.720 --> 15:41.462
Just threatened to cut off
her birds' heads.

15:45.248 --> 15:48.948
She said it in this
really weird voice.

15:59.959 --> 16:02.178
Sarah?

16:04.006 --> 16:05.225
You scared me.

16:05.268 --> 16:08.271
Come out.

16:09.794 --> 16:12.972
Sarah?

16:13.015 --> 16:14.974
Hey, it's not funny.

16:17.889 --> 16:19.195
♪

16:29.945 --> 16:37.692
♪

17:00.758 --> 17:02.891
- Kelly?

17:05.067 --> 17:06.938
Kelly?

17:29.178 --> 17:30.962
- You did this.

17:36.098 --> 17:43.062
♪

18:21.796 --> 18:23.189
Shh, shh, shh.

18:23.232 --> 18:25.147
Settle down.

18:32.023 --> 18:38.378
♪

18:45.036 --> 18:46.864
Where's Sarah?

18:46.908 --> 18:49.171
- Hmm?

18:49.215 --> 18:51.173
- Where's Sarah?
She's not in her room.

18:51.217 --> 18:52.870
- What do you mean?

18:52.914 --> 18:56.352
- I just looked.
She's not in her bedroom.

19:00.051 --> 19:01.357
- Sarah?

19:01.401 --> 19:03.881
♪

19:03.925 --> 19:06.797
- Sarah?

19:06.841 --> 19:08.712
Sarah!

19:08.756 --> 19:10.323
- Sarah?

19:10.366 --> 19:14.327
♪

19:14.370 --> 19:17.330
- Sarah?

19:17.373 --> 19:19.375
Sarah!

19:22.248 --> 19:24.206
Sarah!

19:33.911 --> 19:36.044
Sarah!

19:36.087 --> 19:38.916
Sarah?

19:44.922 --> 19:47.098
Sarah!

20:02.462 --> 20:03.941
Oh.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.813
Sarah.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.655
Oh, come on.

20:30.751 --> 20:34.450
- Hey, what were you
doing out there?

20:34.494 --> 20:36.235
- Hiding.

20:36.278 --> 20:38.237
- What?

20:38.280 --> 20:39.977
- Sarah,

20:40.021 --> 20:42.023
I know you don't like it
here yet,

20:42.066 --> 20:43.981
but you can't be
playing games like this.

20:44.025 --> 20:46.897
- I was hiding
from the darkness.

20:46.941 --> 20:49.248
- What?

20:49.291 --> 20:53.034
- Buster and Chomper warned me.

20:53.077 --> 20:55.689
- The birds told you?

20:59.606 --> 21:01.956
- She doesn't have a fever.

21:01.999 --> 21:05.307
Come on, let's get you upstairs.

21:05.351 --> 21:08.005
We'll talk about this
in the morning.

21:17.145 --> 21:19.321
Come on.

21:19.365 --> 21:22.106
Wake up, sleepyhead.

21:24.631 --> 21:28.461
Feeling better?

21:28.504 --> 21:31.028
You know, after the darkness,

21:31.072 --> 21:33.727
your bad dream and all that.

21:37.948 --> 21:40.342
Was there...

21:40.386 --> 21:43.519
Was there someone
with you last night?

21:43.563 --> 21:46.043
Outside?

21:48.350 --> 21:50.918
- Can I have pancakes?

21:53.529 --> 21:56.010
- After you brush your teeth.

21:56.053 --> 22:03.757
♪

22:20.251 --> 22:23.167
What if Sarah was
sleepwalking last night?

22:23.211 --> 22:26.170
- She seemed pretty awake to me.

22:26.214 --> 22:29.913
- Well...

22:29.957 --> 22:31.151
I mean, she must've done this.

22:31.175 --> 22:32.307
- No, don't even say it.

22:32.351 --> 22:34.396
- Brian, I mean,
we didn't do it.

22:37.051 --> 22:39.706
- We have to send her
to see someone.

22:39.749 --> 22:43.492
There's clearly something wrong.

22:43.536 --> 22:46.277
She decapitated her birds.

22:48.628 --> 22:51.500
She said she was gonna do it.

22:51.544 --> 22:52.545
The other night.

22:52.588 --> 22:55.243
- Wait, wait.

22:55.286 --> 22:59.769
There's blood insidethe cover.

22:59.813 --> 23:03.382
The cover must've been
on the cage when it happened.

23:03.425 --> 23:06.428
- Then where are the heads?

23:19.746 --> 23:22.357
- To Buster and Chomper...

23:24.315 --> 23:26.405
Although we are
no longer together,

23:26.448 --> 23:29.364
you're still here with me,

23:29.408 --> 23:31.148
and wherever you are,

23:31.192 --> 23:33.760
I'm still there with you,

23:33.803 --> 23:36.197
because each and every one of us

23:36.240 --> 23:39.026
leaves an imprint during
the time that we are given.

23:39.069 --> 23:40.593
An imprint that stays

23:40.636 --> 23:44.118
long after our bodies leave us.

23:44.161 --> 23:46.599
So no good-byes
will be said today.

23:53.170 --> 23:55.825
I'll end it there.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.525
Daddy?

23:59.568 --> 24:01.396
We're ready.

24:01.440 --> 24:02.528
- Yeah.

24:02.571 --> 24:05.444
All right.

24:08.447 --> 24:16.411
♪

24:23.549 --> 24:25.420
- Is she asleep?

24:25.464 --> 24:27.248
- Today really wiped her out.

24:27.291 --> 24:28.379
Poor kid.

24:30.643 --> 24:33.472
Well, my sister is comingtomorrow
to check out the house.

24:33.515 --> 24:35.561
So, having her cousin here

24:35.604 --> 24:37.519
will distract her.

24:37.563 --> 24:39.608
- Are they gonna stay
the whole weekend?

24:39.652 --> 24:41.175
- Just one night.

24:41.218 --> 24:43.438
- All right.

24:43.482 --> 24:45.266
What?

24:52.447 --> 24:55.494
Do you wonder if
this was a mistake?

24:55.537 --> 24:58.192
Moving here?

24:59.585 --> 25:01.674
It hasn't even been a month,

25:01.717 --> 25:04.590
and no, I love it.

25:04.633 --> 25:06.766
- But it's just so...
different.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.463
You know, all of her friends

25:08.507 --> 25:10.049
are back in the city,
and my business...

25:10.073 --> 25:12.902
- It's exactly what
I hoped it would be.

25:17.777 --> 25:19.822
- Are you coming to bed?

25:19.866 --> 25:23.739
- I need to do my journal first.

25:23.783 --> 25:26.612
- You could, uh, skip a night.

25:28.918 --> 25:31.138
- It's important to do it
every night.

25:40.843 --> 25:43.367
It's not the city she misses.

25:43.411 --> 25:45.587
It's her business,
because she doesn't have

25:45.631 --> 25:48.285
any massage "therapy"
clients here.

25:51.637 --> 25:54.378
I never told her this,

25:54.422 --> 25:57.425
but sometimes the guys at
work, they'd needle me.

25:57.468 --> 25:59.732
They'd say things
like, you know,

25:59.775 --> 26:03.126
they'd pretend they were gonna
make an appointment with Kelly.

26:04.475 --> 26:06.086
I came home more than once

26:06.129 --> 26:08.523
to find these clients
all oiled up,

26:08.567 --> 26:11.613
and they weren't,
like, old or fat.

26:11.657 --> 26:15.661
These men, these strangers,
they're lying down in a room

26:15.704 --> 26:18.315
next to my wife,
and she's rubbing them down

26:18.359 --> 26:22.189
like a... like you-know-what.

26:22.232 --> 26:25.409
So no, I don't miss
living there.

26:25.453 --> 26:27.977
I don't miss it at all.

26:39.206 --> 26:40.511
- Hi, beautiful.

26:40.555 --> 26:41.730
- Hi, Aunt Jamie.

26:41.774 --> 26:43.645
- I heard your birds died.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.081
- What did I say?

26:45.125 --> 26:46.779
- Not to be a jerk.

26:46.822 --> 26:48.563
- Wanna see something cool?

26:48.607 --> 26:50.609
- Whatever.

26:50.652 --> 26:53.437
- Hey!
- Hey.

26:53.481 --> 26:54.438
- Oh, how are you?

26:54.482 --> 26:55.657
- Good, how are you?

26:55.701 --> 26:56.939
- Good, thanks for coming.
- Hi.

26:56.963 --> 26:59.313
- Of course.
Hello, good to see you.

26:59.356 --> 27:00.880
- Where's Mark?

27:00.923 --> 27:02.795
- He, uh, just couldn't
get away from work.

27:02.838 --> 27:04.448
He said next time, for sure.

27:04.492 --> 27:06.276
Your favorite.

27:06.320 --> 27:08.801
- Oh, it's from the wine store
in our neighborhood.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.846
- Our old neighborhood.

27:12.500 --> 27:14.850
- Well, would you like
to see the grand tour?

27:14.894 --> 27:16.678
- I can't wait.
- All right.

27:33.477 --> 27:36.393
♪

27:36.437 --> 27:37.568
- Whoa.

27:37.612 --> 27:41.572
♪

27:41.616 --> 27:44.227
- My dad says old houses change

27:44.271 --> 27:46.795
and the floors
get crooked and stuff.

27:46.839 --> 27:48.492
♪

27:48.536 --> 27:50.712
- Got any marbles?

27:50.756 --> 27:53.236
- So, how's it all really going?

27:53.280 --> 27:57.545
- Uh, well, aside from
dead pets, no clients,

27:57.588 --> 28:00.374
and Brian finding
a new way to work

28:00.417 --> 28:02.028
every hour of the day.

28:02.071 --> 28:04.552
I guess I just thought
things would be different

28:04.595 --> 28:05.945
when we left the city,

28:05.988 --> 28:09.470
but just more of the same
in a new place.

28:09.513 --> 28:11.559
But our new bathroom

28:11.602 --> 28:13.430
is bigger than
our old living room.

28:13.474 --> 28:14.605
- Nice.

28:14.649 --> 28:17.608
- Give me one.

28:34.495 --> 28:35.801
Cool.

28:35.844 --> 28:36.889
Give me another.

28:36.932 --> 28:39.108
- My turn.

28:42.938 --> 28:50.903
♪

28:53.035 --> 28:54.428
- Awesome.

28:54.471 --> 28:56.647
It's like a magnet.

28:56.691 --> 28:59.476
- Mason, wait.

29:04.960 --> 29:07.746
Mason, don't go down there.

29:11.314 --> 29:13.708
- Where's the stupid lights?

29:20.280 --> 29:22.543
Sarah, open the door.

29:24.327 --> 29:25.851
Sarah?

29:25.894 --> 29:27.548
Sarah!

29:27.591 --> 29:28.549
Sarah, let me out!

29:28.592 --> 29:30.725
Let me out!

29:33.989 --> 29:36.775
- I said, "Don't go down there."

29:36.818 --> 29:38.646
- What'd you say, hun?

29:38.689 --> 29:41.823
- Where's Mason?

29:41.867 --> 29:43.825
- In the dark.

29:46.610 --> 29:49.570
- Mason?

29:56.751 --> 29:59.275
Mase?

30:02.975 --> 30:05.151
Mase?

30:10.417 --> 30:11.548
♪

30:11.592 --> 30:13.159
Mase?

30:18.381 --> 30:20.253
- Oh.

30:22.951 --> 30:24.561
- Hey.

30:24.605 --> 30:27.782
What's wrong?
Come here.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.611
What are you doing down here?

30:30.654 --> 30:32.613
- Uh, I don't know.

30:32.656 --> 30:37.574
♪

30:44.103 --> 30:47.802
- Has he ever done anything
like that before?

30:47.846 --> 30:50.370
Zoned out like that?

30:50.413 --> 30:51.588
- No.

30:51.632 --> 30:55.679
It was definitely weird.

30:55.723 --> 30:58.857
Maybe something's wrong
with your house.

31:08.040 --> 31:12.696
♪

31:53.999 --> 31:56.871
So what happened
at camp with Mason?

31:56.915 --> 31:58.917
- Well, he put a firecracker
in a bullfrog.

31:58.960 --> 32:01.049
- Oh! Oh, no.
- Yes, he did.

32:01.093 --> 32:03.747
Ah, look who has perfect timing

32:03.791 --> 32:05.836
to not help us
make dinner at all.

32:05.880 --> 32:08.013
- I was working.

32:08.056 --> 32:09.057
How you feeling?

32:09.101 --> 32:10.711
- Eh, I'm a little sore.

32:10.754 --> 32:12.321
I'll be okay.

32:12.365 --> 32:13.888
- Good, 'cause you know
we've got, um,

32:13.932 --> 32:15.759
work to do later.

32:15.803 --> 32:17.936
- Um, okay, still right here.

32:17.979 --> 32:19.000
- Whoa, all right,
Prince Charming.

32:19.024 --> 32:20.155
- What?

32:20.199 --> 32:21.479
- You actually
out there working,

32:21.504 --> 32:23.158
or you just drinking
by yourself?

32:23.202 --> 32:24.768
- Well, it's not drinking alone

32:24.812 --> 32:26.683
if there's other people
on the property.

32:26.727 --> 32:27.858
- Hmm.

32:27.902 --> 32:28.947
- This is so much better

32:28.990 --> 32:30.339
than office life.

32:30.383 --> 32:33.168
- Uh, the kids are
in the other room.

32:33.212 --> 32:35.475
Why don't you
call them in for dinner?

32:35.518 --> 32:37.564
Just don't breathe on them.

32:41.046 --> 32:43.222
"It's not drinking alone

32:43.265 --> 32:44.895
if there are other people
on the property"?

32:44.919 --> 32:48.357
I mean, who says that?

32:48.401 --> 32:51.926
And then,
Jamie goes to bed early,

32:51.970 --> 32:54.624
and I'm like,

32:54.668 --> 32:57.279
figuring, okay, you know,

32:57.323 --> 33:01.892
tonight's a night that we will
actually have some alone time,

33:01.936 --> 33:06.114
and he just goes
back to the workshop.

33:08.987 --> 33:11.902
Hey!

33:14.993 --> 33:16.995
You guys are supposed to be
in bed.

33:26.787 --> 33:34.490
♪

33:44.805 --> 33:46.285
Oh, great.

33:46.328 --> 33:49.244
You guys found
an even creepier mask.

33:49.288 --> 33:51.072
It's time for bed, you guys.

35:23.251 --> 35:26.385
Brian.

35:26.428 --> 35:28.256
Brian.

35:28.300 --> 35:30.780
I don't know what...

35:30.824 --> 35:33.174
I saw children

35:33.218 --> 35:35.089
in the hallway.

35:35.133 --> 35:36.873
Wearing masks.

35:36.917 --> 35:39.485
- Okay, did you tell them
to go back to bed?

35:39.528 --> 35:41.530
- It wasn't Mason and Sarah.

35:41.574 --> 35:43.706
I checked.
They're still asleep.

35:45.534 --> 35:47.971
- And you nag me about drinking.

35:48.015 --> 35:49.277
- I'm not drunk.

35:49.321 --> 35:51.018
- Well, neither am I,

35:51.061 --> 35:53.325
and Clark is in the guest room
with Jamie.

35:53.368 --> 35:55.283
- What?
Who?

35:55.327 --> 35:57.329
- Oh, you know who.

35:57.372 --> 35:59.809
- Our neighbor, Clark?

35:59.853 --> 36:02.290
- Shirtless right now
with your sister.

36:02.334 --> 36:05.119
That is obviously crazy.

36:05.163 --> 36:06.381
- Kelly,

36:06.425 --> 36:08.470
he's in there right now.

36:08.514 --> 36:10.231
She's cheating on her husband
with a stranger

36:10.255 --> 36:11.952
in our home.

36:11.995 --> 36:13.823
- Okay.

36:13.867 --> 36:15.956
Now is the time that you admit
that you are joking,

36:15.999 --> 36:17.368
because you're starting
to scare me.

36:17.392 --> 36:20.352
- Go look for yourself.

36:23.137 --> 36:25.270
♪

36:26.271 --> 36:29.056
- Jamie?

36:29.099 --> 36:31.319
It's me.

36:31.363 --> 36:34.104
You up?

36:34.148 --> 36:36.585
Uh, hold on.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.587
- This is ridiculous.

36:40.198 --> 36:42.156
- What's up?

36:42.200 --> 36:44.027
- Where is he?
- Uh, what?

36:44.071 --> 36:45.333
- Brian, enough.

36:45.377 --> 36:47.030
Let it go, okay.

36:47.074 --> 36:48.206
- He's a creep, Jamie.

36:48.249 --> 36:50.208
I already caught him
staring at Kelly.

36:50.251 --> 36:52.949
- Hey, Brian, what in the hell
are you talking about?

36:52.993 --> 36:54.188
- You're drunk and
you're embarrassing me.

36:54.212 --> 36:55.125
Will you stop it?

36:55.169 --> 36:58.303
- Hey! Hey!

36:58.346 --> 37:00.609
Look.
- What?

37:00.653 --> 37:02.350
- Maybe your therapist
can explain

37:02.394 --> 37:03.525
this is called projecting.

37:03.569 --> 37:04.589
Mark and I aren't the ones

37:04.613 --> 37:06.049
having problems.

37:06.093 --> 37:07.244
- Then why didn't he come visit?

37:07.268 --> 37:09.009
- Because he can't stand you

37:09.052 --> 37:10.619
because you're a jealous prick.

37:10.663 --> 37:13.143
- Well, at least
I'm not a cheater.

37:14.449 --> 37:17.235
- You've lost your mind, dude.

37:17.278 --> 37:19.324
You know, and if you think
giving up your business

37:19.367 --> 37:21.258
and moving to the sticks
to have another kid with him

37:21.282 --> 37:22.588
is going to fix anything,

37:22.631 --> 37:25.417
you're just as crazy as he is.

37:25.460 --> 37:27.506
Mason?

37:27.549 --> 37:28.985
- Mason, wake up, honey.

37:29.029 --> 37:30.378
We have to go.

37:30.422 --> 37:32.250
Jamie!

37:42.303 --> 37:44.262
Jamie, please.

37:45.524 --> 37:47.265
Come on, just wait
until morning.

37:47.308 --> 37:49.484
Jamie, please stay.

37:49.528 --> 37:51.114
Look, I'm so sorry.
I know that he's an...

37:51.138 --> 37:54.141
Jamie! Jamie!

38:00.626 --> 38:03.846
- Dad?

38:03.890 --> 38:06.719
What in the hell
were you thinking?

38:06.762 --> 38:08.242
That is my sister.

38:09.287 --> 38:11.898
- Brian?

38:11.941 --> 38:14.466
Brian, will you please
just talk to me?

38:14.509 --> 38:16.076
What in the hell is going...

38:16.119 --> 38:19.993
Brian!

38:20.036 --> 38:21.436
What is going on
with you right now?

38:21.473 --> 38:23.083
Have you lost your mind?

38:23.126 --> 38:25.128
That's my sister.

38:25.172 --> 38:27.696
Brian! Brian!

38:37.663 --> 38:40.100
You can sleep on the couch!

38:44.670 --> 38:47.716
- Aah!

38:51.764 --> 38:55.202
- You feeling better?

38:55.245 --> 38:57.422
After your bad dream?

39:01.774 --> 39:04.516
- Why did they have to go
in the middle of the night?

39:05.734 --> 39:08.084
- Um...

39:09.912 --> 39:11.740
Your Aunt Jamie
wasn't feeling good.

39:11.784 --> 39:15.614
- Then she probably needs sleep.

39:15.657 --> 39:18.878
- You are so smart, buddy.

39:18.921 --> 39:20.575
How about we go into town today?

39:20.619 --> 39:23.273
Maybe catch a movie?

39:23.317 --> 39:24.405
- Yes, please.

39:24.449 --> 39:27.626
Can Dad come?

39:27.669 --> 39:31.630
- Uh, he probably needs to work.

39:33.806 --> 39:35.416
He always needs to work.

39:45.687 --> 39:46.514
- Then we went to the library,

39:46.558 --> 39:48.647
and I got three books.

39:48.690 --> 39:50.257
- Big ones or little ones?

39:50.300 --> 39:51.432
- I'm nine.

39:51.476 --> 39:52.477
- So, big ones.

39:53.652 --> 39:55.610
And then we ate pizza at,

39:55.654 --> 39:57.699
um...

39:57.743 --> 39:58.787
- It's called Garabusi's.

39:58.831 --> 40:00.441
- Right.

40:00.485 --> 40:02.487
Mommy let me get
whatever I wanted.

40:02.530 --> 40:07.448
- That's because your mom is
the coolest person in the world.

40:07.492 --> 40:10.756
- And then we saw a movie.

40:10.799 --> 40:13.585
- That was a pretty amazing day.

40:13.628 --> 40:17.240
- Too bad you weren't there.

40:17.284 --> 40:20.766
- Next time I will be.

40:20.809 --> 40:23.638
I'm sorry I missed it today.

40:28.208 --> 40:30.079
- Honey, you've got work
to do on your table.

40:30.123 --> 40:32.430
We'll get this.

40:35.520 --> 40:43.441
♪

40:58.891 --> 41:01.807
I'm... I'm starting to feel like

41:01.850 --> 41:04.679
I really don't know this man.

41:09.771 --> 41:12.600
And that is scaring me.

41:16.212 --> 41:19.128
- This... this is a disaster.

41:19.172 --> 41:22.523
I feel like it's almost
gone too far

41:22.567 --> 41:24.003
to even get better now.

41:24.046 --> 41:25.657
Like, what are we even
doing, you know?

41:25.700 --> 41:27.876
- Talking to yourself?

41:27.920 --> 41:29.791
- Uh, hi, no.

41:29.835 --> 41:32.359
I was just, uh...

41:32.402 --> 41:35.623
Um...

41:35.667 --> 41:38.670
You're Ellen, right?

41:38.713 --> 41:41.847
- Yes, and you're...

41:41.890 --> 41:43.283
- Brian.
- Brian, right.

41:43.326 --> 41:46.504
Oh, silly, we're neighbors.

41:46.547 --> 41:49.507
Mm.

41:55.861 --> 41:58.690
You don't have any white wine
in that fridge, do you?

41:58.733 --> 42:01.693
It's so hot out here.

42:01.736 --> 42:04.565
- Um, no, just beer.

42:04.609 --> 42:06.349
- That'll work.

42:12.530 --> 42:20.320
♪

42:24.933 --> 42:27.893
Looks like everyone's asleep.

42:27.936 --> 42:30.460
- Um...

42:30.504 --> 42:32.854
Probably, yeah.

42:32.898 --> 42:35.770
- I've been watching you work.

42:37.816 --> 42:40.688
- You have?

42:40.732 --> 42:42.777
- I guess building a business
is like that.

42:42.821 --> 42:45.737
You have to put in
so much effort, right?

42:45.780 --> 42:48.696
- Yeah.

42:48.740 --> 42:50.959
I wish Kelly got that.

42:51.003 --> 42:53.179
♪

42:53.222 --> 42:55.964
- Some people only see
what they choose to see.

42:58.619 --> 43:00.360
But I don't.

43:03.581 --> 43:11.327
♪

43:16.898 --> 43:24.898
♪

43:48.103 --> 43:56.024
♪

44:28.840 --> 44:32.060
- I feel like
something's happening to me.

44:32.104 --> 44:34.584
I don't know what's going on.

44:37.413 --> 44:40.329
I'm gonna hurt them.

44:40.373 --> 44:42.375
It wants me to hurt them.

44:44.594 --> 44:47.554
- Sarah, can you bring down
your dirty clothes?

44:47.597 --> 44:50.557
- Fine.

44:50.600 --> 44:53.212
- Don't forget the ones
on your floor.

45:00.698 --> 45:03.831
- I'll try.

45:20.805 --> 45:22.763
- Here.

45:25.157 --> 45:26.898
Mommy?

45:34.732 --> 45:41.869
♪

45:41.913 --> 45:43.001
- She's asleep?

45:43.044 --> 45:45.438
- Yeah, what's going on?

45:50.356 --> 45:53.185
- I saw a family
in the dining room.

45:53.228 --> 45:56.057
Just like I saw those kids
in the masks upstairs.

45:56.101 --> 45:57.058
- That was Sarah and Mason.

45:57.102 --> 45:59.017
- No, it wasn't,

45:59.060 --> 46:01.802
and as soon as I blinked,

46:01.846 --> 46:04.500
they disappeared.

46:04.544 --> 46:06.720
- So you're saying, what?
You saw a ghost?

46:06.764 --> 46:07.852
- I don't know, Brian.

46:07.895 --> 46:10.419
I don't like it here.

46:12.900 --> 46:14.075
I want to leave.

46:14.119 --> 46:16.121
- This is unbelievable.

46:16.164 --> 46:18.079
- Look, I am seeing things,

46:18.123 --> 46:20.125
and I am not crazy.

46:20.168 --> 46:21.779
- No, just manipulative.

46:21.822 --> 46:24.216
- What?

46:24.259 --> 46:26.087
- We came here
to save our family,

46:26.131 --> 46:27.804
and ever since we moved in,
you've been trying to

46:27.828 --> 46:29.221
find reasons to go back.

46:29.264 --> 46:31.049
Sarah has no friends.
You have no clients.

46:31.092 --> 46:33.051
I work too much.

46:33.094 --> 46:35.009
- Please.

46:35.053 --> 46:37.664
You have to believe me.

46:41.059 --> 46:42.800
There is something

46:42.843 --> 46:45.237
wrong with this house.

46:45.280 --> 46:48.022
- Hey, Kelly, you think
maybe it's you?

46:50.808 --> 46:53.114
- You can stay here.

46:53.158 --> 46:54.986
I'll take Sarah,
and I'll go to the city,

46:55.029 --> 46:56.465
and I'll live with Jamie.

46:56.509 --> 46:57.921
- Because you think
the house is haunted.

46:57.945 --> 46:59.120
Who's crazy now, Kelly?

46:59.164 --> 47:00.252
You know who'd get custody?

47:00.295 --> 47:02.297
- Custody?

47:02.341 --> 47:04.212
Who said anything
about a divorce?

47:04.256 --> 47:05.973
- You're threatening to
take my daughter away.

47:05.997 --> 47:08.869
Hey, look at me.
Look at me.

47:08.913 --> 47:10.697
You know me.

47:10.740 --> 47:13.134
You know who I am,
and you know how I do things.

47:13.178 --> 47:17.660
And I would never, ever let you
take Sarah away from me.

47:17.704 --> 47:19.880
- Look at you.

47:19.924 --> 47:23.623
You're a crazy person.

47:23.666 --> 47:26.800
And you would never get custody.

47:26.844 --> 47:28.517
- Over the woman who took
her child from the house,

47:28.541 --> 47:30.673
without permission,
because she was seeing things

47:30.717 --> 47:33.067
and thought they were ghosts?

47:33.111 --> 47:34.939
Kelly, you're smarter than this.

47:47.908 --> 47:51.825
- You don't threaten
to take Sarah away from me.

47:51.869 --> 47:54.828
You don't threaten
to take Sarah away.

47:54.872 --> 47:57.875
You don't threaten
to take Sarah away from me!

47:57.918 --> 48:00.225
You don't take Sarah
away from me, Kelly!

48:00.268 --> 48:01.879
You hear me?

48:01.922 --> 48:03.489
- Brian, get out!

48:03.532 --> 48:05.273
- You don't threaten
to break up this family

48:05.317 --> 48:07.754
because you're trying
to ruin my dreams!

48:07.797 --> 48:09.538
My dreams!

48:09.582 --> 48:11.671
- Daddy?

48:16.023 --> 48:17.938
♪

48:17.982 --> 48:19.220
- You should be in bed, sweetie.

48:19.244 --> 48:21.550
- But...
- It's okay.

48:21.594 --> 48:23.857
Daddy's gonna go downstairs
and get some sleep.

48:23.901 --> 48:26.294
It's okay.

48:26.338 --> 48:29.036
Go to bed.
It's all right.

48:29.080 --> 48:32.518
♪

48:56.585 --> 48:59.284
- You awake, Kelly?

49:01.851 --> 49:04.506
I think we need to talk
about this now.

49:06.944 --> 49:09.120
Sleeping in separate beds,

49:09.163 --> 49:11.905
it isn't gonna fix anything.

49:16.910 --> 49:19.652
Come on, Kelly.

49:22.611 --> 49:25.527
Kelly, please.

49:28.574 --> 49:30.663
♪

49:31.925 --> 49:35.842
♪

49:46.809 --> 49:54.687
♪

50:29.809 --> 50:37.599
♪

50:54.225 --> 50:56.662
- Dad?

50:58.185 --> 51:00.666
- Sweetie, I'm working.

51:00.709 --> 51:03.408
- Mommy got a client.

51:06.063 --> 51:09.240
- That's great.

51:09.283 --> 51:13.113
- Okay, well, we're going
to get some oils and stuff,

51:13.157 --> 51:15.942
and I hope some ice cream too.

51:18.727 --> 51:19.728
- Love you.

51:26.213 --> 51:28.302
♪

51:28.346 --> 51:30.043
- And all of our soaps and oils

51:30.087 --> 51:31.653
are actually made
right here in town.

51:31.697 --> 51:33.699
- Oh, that's great.

51:33.742 --> 51:35.788
I'll definitely be back.

51:35.831 --> 51:37.287
- Well, I can ship them
to you too, if it's easier.

51:37.311 --> 51:38.791
- Oh, there's no need.

51:38.834 --> 51:40.706
We, uh, just moved here
a few weeks ago.

51:40.749 --> 51:42.360
- Oh, congratulations.

51:42.403 --> 51:45.014
It's a great place to live
most of the time.

51:45.058 --> 51:46.166
What part of town are you in?

51:46.190 --> 51:47.756
- Um, we just

51:47.800 --> 51:49.106
bought a farm house over on,

51:49.149 --> 51:50.300
uh, Church and Ballard Street.

51:50.324 --> 51:54.111
My husband needed a workshop.

51:54.154 --> 51:56.374
Do you know the place?

51:56.417 --> 51:58.767
- Mm-hmm.
Thanks for coming in.

51:58.811 --> 52:00.029
- Thanks.

52:00.073 --> 52:01.814
- Excuse me, can you
not do that?

52:01.857 --> 52:04.164
- Sarah, hey.

52:04.208 --> 52:07.211
Sarah, that's not yours.

52:07.254 --> 52:08.690
Sarah?

52:10.214 --> 52:13.173
Why did you write that?

52:15.175 --> 52:17.656
Uh, I'm really sorry.

52:21.094 --> 52:23.227
Come on.

52:23.270 --> 52:29.842
♪

52:29.885 --> 52:31.017
Sarah?

52:35.064 --> 52:37.371
Where did you hear that?

52:37.415 --> 52:40.200
"We see what we choose to see."

52:40.244 --> 52:43.116
- What?

52:43.160 --> 52:45.858
- The thing that you wrote.

52:49.383 --> 52:52.691
- Can we still get ice cream?

53:03.136 --> 53:11.100
♪

53:14.278 --> 53:16.802
- Mm-hmm.

53:23.330 --> 53:25.245
Ugh!
Nothing again.

53:25.289 --> 53:28.248
Unbelievable.

53:28.292 --> 53:30.337
Anyone need anything?

53:30.381 --> 53:31.904
- I'll take a water.

53:31.947 --> 53:32.992
Please.

53:33.035 --> 53:34.950
- I'm fine.

53:34.994 --> 53:36.082
- Okay.

53:43.307 --> 53:45.918
- Yes.

53:45.961 --> 53:48.094
- Okay.

53:51.315 --> 53:52.968
- Daddy's turn.

53:53.012 --> 53:54.796
- Brian, it's your turn.

53:56.363 --> 53:58.322
- Dad?

54:00.237 --> 54:01.238
- Hang on.

54:01.281 --> 54:03.414
I'll be right back.

54:24.913 --> 54:32.660
♪

54:43.584 --> 54:45.978
I thought you were
coming back to game night.

54:49.111 --> 54:52.071
- Brian!

54:54.291 --> 54:56.162
What are you doing?

54:56.205 --> 54:58.338
- Nothing, uh...

54:58.382 --> 54:59.992
Nothing.

55:00.035 --> 55:01.907
- Was there someone in here?

55:01.950 --> 55:04.649
- No.

55:11.569 --> 55:14.398
- I saw you talking to someone.

55:14.441 --> 55:18.053
- Well... well, you saw wrong.

55:18.097 --> 55:25.887
♪

55:42.948 --> 55:47.474
♪

55:47.518 --> 55:52.044
- I... I know how this all sounds,

55:52.087 --> 55:54.960
but...

55:55.003 --> 55:56.962
I've seen things, Jamie.

55:57.005 --> 55:58.180
- Call someone in.

55:58.224 --> 56:00.618
- Like who?

56:00.661 --> 56:03.621
- Brian wasn't all wrong
about me and Mark.

56:03.664 --> 56:07.364
There was a problem,
like, a year ago.

56:07.407 --> 56:09.104
- You never told me.

56:09.148 --> 56:11.237
- Not everything
needs to be broadcast,

56:11.280 --> 56:14.980
but you know, don't laugh.

56:15.023 --> 56:16.242
I talked to a psychic.

56:18.418 --> 56:22.030
- Seriously, Kelly,
everything she said was true.

56:22.074 --> 56:24.729
Pay her to make the trip.

56:33.825 --> 56:36.567
♪

56:36.610 --> 56:39.918
So, I can't believe this,

56:39.961 --> 56:43.182
but I actually
sent Sarah and Brian out

56:43.225 --> 56:45.265
on a bunch of errands to
get them out of the house.

56:48.927 --> 56:51.669
And this woman, um...

56:54.802 --> 56:59.372
A psychic... is coming here.

57:04.725 --> 57:11.471
♪

57:11.515 --> 57:13.647
- There were two of them.

57:13.691 --> 57:15.170
- Yeah.

57:15.214 --> 57:18.260
- They were warning
your daughter.

57:18.304 --> 57:21.829
It killed them to keep
from warning her again.

57:21.873 --> 57:29.837
♪

57:38.542 --> 57:41.893
He stays downstairs now?

57:41.936 --> 57:45.853
- Uh... well,
we've had some fights.

57:45.897 --> 57:48.552
- But he's been in here
at night...

57:48.595 --> 57:50.597
watching you sleep.

57:50.641 --> 57:56.995
♪

57:57.038 --> 57:58.953
There are children here.

57:58.997 --> 58:01.608
Young spirits.

58:01.652 --> 58:04.916
They're hiding behind masks.

58:06.700 --> 58:08.920
Oh, no.

58:08.963 --> 58:12.010
They're all trapped in here,

58:12.053 --> 58:14.752
and they're not alone.

58:14.795 --> 58:18.712
There's something
looming over this place.

58:18.756 --> 58:20.801
This land.

58:27.286 --> 58:29.810
- What?

58:29.854 --> 58:31.508
What is it?

58:31.551 --> 58:34.598
- A shadow.

58:34.641 --> 58:35.903
Just...

58:35.947 --> 58:39.864
darkness.

58:39.907 --> 58:42.083
It's a soul collector,

58:42.127 --> 58:44.912
and it's not done.

58:44.956 --> 58:47.132
- I don't understand.

58:47.175 --> 58:48.742
Who is it?

58:48.786 --> 58:50.135
- No, no, it's not a who.

58:50.178 --> 58:51.789
It's, um...

58:51.832 --> 58:53.834
It's a what.

58:53.878 --> 58:57.272
I don't know, but it's been
here longer than you or me.

59:00.232 --> 59:02.669
It's pure darkness.

59:05.846 --> 59:08.109
- What does it want?

59:08.153 --> 59:10.764
- It wants death.

59:10.808 --> 59:13.854
It wants pain.

59:13.898 --> 59:15.160
And it preys on the weak.

59:15.203 --> 59:17.771
It infects them

59:17.815 --> 59:19.207
like a virus.

59:19.251 --> 59:21.209
You hear that?

59:21.253 --> 59:23.864
- Hear what?
- He's here.

59:23.908 --> 59:25.170
- Are you okay?
- Oh!

59:25.213 --> 59:28.652
Oh, that buzzing.

59:28.695 --> 59:31.916
He's here, he's here.

59:31.959 --> 59:34.266
I have to go.
I have to...

59:34.309 --> 59:36.050
- No, just...
- I have to go.

59:36.094 --> 59:37.530
- Can't you just stay?

59:37.574 --> 59:39.837
- No, no, now I have to go.
I have to be...

59:39.880 --> 59:41.490
- No, please,
I don't even understand!

59:41.534 --> 59:43.033
- I have to go now!
- But please, I need your help!

59:43.057 --> 59:44.929
I don't understand.

59:44.972 --> 59:47.671
- Stop.
Oh, my God, no!

59:49.760 --> 59:51.022
- Oh, no!

59:51.065 --> 59:53.633
- No, no!

59:53.677 --> 59:55.635
Oh, my God!

59:55.679 --> 59:57.594
- Open the door!

59:57.637 --> 59:59.900
Open the door!

59:59.944 --> 01:00:02.947
- Aah!
Aah!

01:00:14.045 --> 01:00:16.351
- Okay, just breathe normal.

01:00:16.395 --> 01:00:17.918
Okay, relax and breathe normal.

01:00:17.962 --> 01:00:20.138
There you go.

01:00:23.228 --> 01:00:31.192
♪

01:00:43.640 --> 01:00:45.729
♪

01:00:45.772 --> 01:00:47.992
I didn't tell her anything

01:00:48.035 --> 01:00:50.821
about what I have seen or heard.

01:00:50.864 --> 01:00:52.866
She just walked through
the house, and she knew.

01:00:55.042 --> 01:00:56.367
She knows your sister,
though, right?

01:00:56.391 --> 01:00:58.872
- So?

01:00:58.916 --> 01:01:01.745
- So, these people
are con artists, Kelly.

01:01:01.788 --> 01:01:03.616
They gather information
from everywhere

01:01:03.660 --> 01:01:05.159
and stitch it together
so you think they got a gift.

01:01:05.183 --> 01:01:07.751
- She ran out of the house

01:01:07.794 --> 01:01:09.163
because she heard
a buzzing in her head.

01:01:09.187 --> 01:01:10.754
- Theater.

01:01:10.797 --> 01:01:12.514
And before she could
hit you up for big money

01:01:12.538 --> 01:01:16.237
to perform an exorcism
or whatever, she got stung.

01:01:16.281 --> 01:01:18.849
- I want to move.

01:01:18.892 --> 01:01:22.853
- You've wanted to move
since we got here.

01:01:22.896 --> 01:01:27.248
- I am trying to
save our family here.

01:01:27.292 --> 01:01:30.251
We have to leave.

01:01:32.906 --> 01:01:34.952
- Actually,

01:01:34.995 --> 01:01:36.780
I have to stay.

01:01:39.173 --> 01:01:40.324
- While I was out with Sarah,

01:01:40.348 --> 01:01:41.915
we stopped by a new restaurant

01:01:41.959 --> 01:01:43.327
that's supposed to
open this winter.

01:01:43.351 --> 01:01:44.701
Showed the owner some pics,

01:01:44.744 --> 01:01:47.791
he placed an order.

01:01:47.834 --> 01:01:50.402
Tables, chairs, a custom bar.

01:01:50.445 --> 01:01:52.317
It's huge.

01:01:57.844 --> 01:02:00.325
You might be...

01:02:00.368 --> 01:02:03.763
the most selfish man
in the world.

01:02:03.807 --> 01:02:11.510
♪

01:02:41.932 --> 01:02:48.373
♪

01:02:48.416 --> 01:02:50.984
Sarah!

01:02:51.028 --> 01:02:52.769
Sarah!

01:03:03.040 --> 01:03:04.737
- She's not in the house.

01:03:04.781 --> 01:03:07.348
- He took her.
You're wasting your time.

01:03:07.392 --> 01:03:10.438
- How well do you know
your neighbors?

01:03:10.482 --> 01:03:12.963
- Hey, everyone quiet!

01:03:13.006 --> 01:03:14.399
- What is it?
- Shh.

01:03:22.973 --> 01:03:29.893
♪

01:03:29.936 --> 01:03:30.937
- Sarah?

01:03:30.981 --> 01:03:32.156
- Sarah!

01:03:32.199 --> 01:03:34.245
- Sarah, you down here?

01:03:34.288 --> 01:03:41.948
♪

01:03:45.560 --> 01:03:46.953
- She's in the wall.

01:03:46.997 --> 01:03:49.173
- What?

01:03:49.216 --> 01:03:51.131
Sarah?

01:03:56.136 --> 01:03:57.398
How?

01:03:57.442 --> 01:03:59.661
Oh, my God.

01:04:13.110 --> 01:04:14.851
Is she in there?

01:04:45.969 --> 01:04:47.013
- She's in there.

01:04:47.057 --> 01:04:48.972
- Sarah!

01:04:49.015 --> 01:04:50.974
- Sarah!

01:04:53.890 --> 01:04:56.849
What were you doing in there?

01:04:59.896 --> 01:05:01.985
- It's the safe place.

01:05:02.028 --> 01:05:04.030
- What?

01:05:04.074 --> 01:05:09.427
♪

01:05:09.470 --> 01:05:12.343
How did you get in there?

01:05:21.308 --> 01:05:29.229
♪

01:05:48.205 --> 01:05:51.121
- "We see what
we choose to see."

01:05:51.164 --> 01:05:53.427
♪

01:05:53.471 --> 01:05:56.169
Whatever that means.

01:06:04.003 --> 01:06:05.657
- It doesn't make any sense.

01:06:05.700 --> 01:06:07.006
How did she get in there?

01:06:07.050 --> 01:06:08.573
There was no hole in the wall.

01:06:08.616 --> 01:06:10.531
There was no way in or out.

01:06:10.575 --> 01:06:14.100
It was like
someone sealed her in.

01:06:14.144 --> 01:06:18.322
- Your, um, house is pretty
well known in this town.

01:06:18.365 --> 01:06:20.977
My father used to
always say, uh...

01:06:21.020 --> 01:06:24.328
there's something just
wrong with this place.

01:06:24.371 --> 01:06:26.373
- Here we go again.

01:06:26.417 --> 01:06:28.462
- My father was the Chief,

01:06:28.506 --> 01:06:30.073
a long time ago,

01:06:30.116 --> 01:06:31.552
and the biggest case
of his career

01:06:31.596 --> 01:06:33.728
was in the late 50s.

01:06:33.772 --> 01:06:36.079
It was right here at this house.

01:06:36.122 --> 01:06:38.951
A man named Andrew Keating,

01:06:38.995 --> 01:06:41.562
he was the principal
at the elementary school,

01:06:41.606 --> 01:06:44.739
and, um, he lived here alone.

01:06:44.783 --> 01:06:48.526
People always said he was a...

01:06:48.569 --> 01:06:52.051
a good man, a normal man.

01:06:52.095 --> 01:06:56.403
Then in 1957,
two kids went missing.

01:06:56.447 --> 01:06:58.666
- You first.

01:06:58.710 --> 01:07:01.408
The night of Halloween.

01:07:06.326 --> 01:07:09.329
A good two weeks went by,

01:07:09.373 --> 01:07:12.724
before anyone realized that
Andrew hadn't shown up for work.

01:07:12.767 --> 01:07:16.249
So my father and his men,
they came down here.

01:07:16.293 --> 01:07:19.252
There was no answer.

01:07:19.296 --> 01:07:21.472
The door was double-locked.

01:07:21.515 --> 01:07:24.518
So they broke in,

01:07:24.562 --> 01:07:28.044
and the kids were here.

01:07:28.087 --> 01:07:30.133
Dead.

01:07:32.396 --> 01:07:35.442
Still in their costumes.

01:07:35.486 --> 01:07:39.533
My father said that
it took a while to find Andrew.

01:07:39.577 --> 01:07:43.537
He had barred himself
in a room and...

01:07:43.581 --> 01:07:45.409
starved himself to death.

01:07:45.452 --> 01:07:47.193
It's the safe place.

01:07:47.237 --> 01:07:48.760
- There's a reason

01:07:48.803 --> 01:07:52.633
this house is
so infamous in town.

01:07:52.677 --> 01:07:55.636
It wasn't just Andrew Keating.

01:07:55.680 --> 01:07:59.118
20 years later, a woman named...

01:07:59.162 --> 01:08:01.860
That's enough of that.

01:08:01.903 --> 01:08:04.906
I'm just glad that this
young lady is safe and sound.

01:08:07.300 --> 01:08:09.215
You're a craftsman?

01:08:09.259 --> 01:08:10.695
- Yeah.

01:08:10.738 --> 01:08:12.784
- Seal up that room.

01:08:12.827 --> 01:08:15.482
It's a dangerous place to play.

01:08:22.272 --> 01:08:25.318
Ruth Wallace.

01:08:25.362 --> 01:08:28.060
Let's go.

01:08:30.584 --> 01:08:33.326
- Sarah couldn't explain
how she got in the room.

01:08:36.676 --> 01:08:38.810
There were no holes

01:08:38.853 --> 01:08:41.421
in any of the walls.

01:08:42.901 --> 01:08:45.817
She said she just blacked out.

01:08:48.124 --> 01:08:52.649
And then the cop
mentioned that name,

01:08:52.693 --> 01:08:55.653
Ruth Wallace.

01:08:58.134 --> 01:09:00.136
Apparently, she's still alive.

01:09:00.179 --> 01:09:01.484
No! Let me out!

01:09:04.488 --> 01:09:06.925
- She hasn't had a visitor
in a lot of years.

01:09:06.968 --> 01:09:09.362
I gotta warn you,
she almost never speaks.

01:09:15.455 --> 01:09:17.849
- Why isn't she in
a mental institution?

01:09:17.892 --> 01:09:20.024
- From what I've heard,
the public defender

01:09:20.068 --> 01:09:21.809
tried to plead insanity
on her behalf,

01:09:21.853 --> 01:09:23.420
but the judge didn't buy it.

01:09:23.462 --> 01:09:25.595
And the attacks
haven't helped her case

01:09:25.639 --> 01:09:27.598
to get out of here
and into an institution.

01:09:27.640 --> 01:09:29.991
- Hey!

01:09:30.035 --> 01:09:32.559
- Once every year or so,
something sets her off

01:09:32.603 --> 01:09:34.344
and she attacks someone.

01:09:34.386 --> 01:09:35.736
A guard,

01:09:35.779 --> 01:09:38.261
another inmate.

01:09:44.397 --> 01:09:46.399
I'll be back in ten minutes.

01:09:46.443 --> 01:09:49.185
If you want out sooner
just rap on the door.

01:09:55.408 --> 01:10:03.408
♪

01:10:03.634 --> 01:10:06.332
- My family and I
moved into a house.

01:10:08.378 --> 01:10:10.336
It's the same one

01:10:10.380 --> 01:10:13.513
that you used to live in.

01:10:18.257 --> 01:10:21.260
I know what you did there.

01:10:21.304 --> 01:10:24.785
I know

01:10:24.829 --> 01:10:27.701
what happened before.

01:10:27.745 --> 01:10:31.792
With the man and those children.

01:10:39.278 --> 01:10:42.890
What do the symbols mean?

01:10:42.934 --> 01:10:45.284
I've seen them before.

01:10:45.328 --> 01:10:47.417
In the basement.

01:10:56.774 --> 01:11:00.299
I've seen your family...

01:11:00.343 --> 01:11:02.736
sitting around
the dining room table.

01:11:06.305 --> 01:11:09.221
- I didn't poison them,

01:11:09.265 --> 01:11:11.745
but I poisoned them.

01:11:13.791 --> 01:11:21.755
♪

01:11:23.670 --> 01:11:26.499
- You're a sensitive.

01:11:26.543 --> 01:11:29.850
- A what?

01:11:29.894 --> 01:11:33.811
- You see things.

01:11:33.854 --> 01:11:37.554
- Not until this house.

01:11:37.597 --> 01:11:40.339
- Well...

01:11:40.383 --> 01:11:44.300
There's something there.

01:11:44.343 --> 01:11:47.564
Something powerful.

01:11:47.607 --> 01:11:55.607
♪

01:11:55.702 --> 01:11:58.662
And the basement...

01:11:58.705 --> 01:12:01.621
is the safe room.

01:12:04.711 --> 01:12:08.367
It's the only safe room.

01:12:08.411 --> 01:12:14.242
♪

01:12:14.286 --> 01:12:17.028
There's something dark
in that house.

01:12:18.812 --> 01:12:20.379
Don't run in the house!

01:12:20.423 --> 01:12:23.991
It got inside my mind.

01:12:24.035 --> 01:12:28.518
It wanted me to hurt my family.

01:12:28.561 --> 01:12:31.564
It wanted me to kill
my own children.

01:12:33.958 --> 01:12:35.655
I put poison in the food.

01:12:37.744 --> 01:12:41.008
I could feel it.

01:12:43.489 --> 01:12:46.666
The phone rang and
it snapped me out of it.

01:12:48.451 --> 01:12:49.930
I poisoned myself

01:12:49.974 --> 01:12:52.716
to save my family from
what I would do.

01:12:53.978 --> 01:12:56.502
I had to protect them...

01:12:56.546 --> 01:12:58.635
from the darkness.

01:12:58.678 --> 01:13:01.638
I knew it wouldn't leave me
alone until I killed them.

01:13:01.681 --> 01:13:03.596
So I had to kill myself.

01:13:03.640 --> 01:13:05.555
No!

01:13:05.598 --> 01:13:07.339
I threw the poisoned food away.

01:13:07.383 --> 01:13:09.863
I know I did.

01:13:09.907 --> 01:13:13.650
I went to the basement to die.

01:13:18.437 --> 01:13:21.919
The darkness wanted pain.

01:13:21.962 --> 01:13:24.922
It wanted death.

01:13:26.532 --> 01:13:28.404
Once it's in you,

01:13:28.447 --> 01:13:29.709
you can't get it out.

01:13:32.625 --> 01:13:37.891
♪

01:13:37.935 --> 01:13:41.242
It didn't let me die.

01:13:43.767 --> 01:13:49.033
When I came back,
they were all dead.

01:13:57.824 --> 01:14:02.438
I... I didn't poison them...

01:14:03.917 --> 01:14:07.878
But I poisoned them.

01:14:07.921 --> 01:14:12.926
♪

01:14:12.970 --> 01:14:14.754
- What does that mean?

01:14:14.798 --> 01:14:16.800
Ruth?
Ruth?

01:14:16.843 --> 01:14:17.975
What do those words mean?

01:14:18.976 --> 01:14:20.891
- That's it for time.

01:14:20.934 --> 01:14:22.806
- No, not yet, please.
She was talking.

01:14:22.849 --> 01:14:25.069
Ruth, what does it mean?

01:14:30.857 --> 01:14:34.905
- Your child is not safe.

01:14:37.951 --> 01:14:45.916
♪

01:14:56.056 --> 01:14:58.189
- Hi, this is Brian.

01:14:58.232 --> 01:15:01.235
Leave me a message
and I'll call you back.

01:15:01.279 --> 01:15:03.411
Please.

01:15:03.455 --> 01:15:05.849
Please, answer.

01:15:05.892 --> 01:15:07.154
